HTML

HTML stands for Hypertext Markup Language.
HTML used to build the web pages.
Web pages will provide the services over the web
In general,we will prepare web pages by using tags

Stntax.
-
    <starting_element>Content</ending_element>



Ex.


1.<html></html>

    - This tag is the root element of web page
    - This tag contain two sections of web page.
     1. Head section.
     2. Body section

Head section:
Used to define the meta data of web page.

Body section:
Used to define the content of web page.



2. <head></head>

    - Used to define the head section of web page.

 3. <title></title>
    -Used to define the title for web page.

 4. <body></body>
    - Used to define the content of web page.


Syntax.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

    <head>
        <title>Demo Web Page</title>
    </head>

    <body>
        Welcome to First Web Page !
    </body>
</html>



Heading in HTML.
-
    <h1></h1> to <h6></h6>

        - USed to define the headings in web page.


Self Declarative Elements.
-
<b></b>

        - used to make the text as bold

<i></i>

        - used to make the text as italic

<u></u>

        - used to make the text the underlined


<font></font>

        - to use the perticular font while developing the web page.

 <label></label>

         - used to define the labels in web page.

 &nbsp;

        -used to make the single space in web page

 &emsp;

      - used to make the tab space in web page.


 Attributes.

    - Attributes are used to enhance the HTML Capabilities.

 Ex.

    <html lang="en">

    <font>Hello</font>

    <font color='red'>Hello</font>

    <font style="color:red;style=bold">Hello</font>



<input></input>

    - used to create the input fields in web page.


Ex.

    <input type="text">   //Used to Enter the Text

    <input type="password">  //Used to Enter the Password

    <input type="number">   // used to enter the Numerical Values

    <input type="date">     //used to open the Date Picker to select the Date.

    <input type="color">   //used to open the color picker

    <input type="radio">  // used to create the radio buttons

    <input type="checkbox">  // used to create the checkboxes

    <input type="button">   // used to create the clickable buttons


 <button></button> - used to create the Buttons.

    <input type="text" id="my_text">









































